%% 3.2.10 Buy Service Package — sequence
%% POST /api/Order/Create OrderCreateDto (GuardianId, StudentId, PackageId) — wallet debit, Order PAID
%% Route/station wizard: not in OrderCreateDto — use StudentBusAssignment (POST) after purchase
%% BR55: Sufficient balance — OrderService checks wallet.Balance >= package.Price

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Guardian as Guardian
    participant App as Mobile App
    participant OC as OrderController
    participant OS as OrderService
    participant Repo as Order Wallet Package Student
    participant DB as SQL Server

    Guardian->>App: Select child, package, confirm (route/station UI → assignment later)
    App->>OC: POST /api/Order/Create OrderCreateDto
    OC->>OS: CreateOrderAsync
    OS->>Repo: Validate guardian, student, package
    OS->>Repo: Wallet balance check (BR55)
    alt Insufficient funds
        OS-->>OC: throw
        OC-->>App: 400 Bad Request
    else Sufficient funds
        OS->>Repo: Debit wallet + Order PAID + Payment + TransactionLog
        Repo->>DB: UPDATE / INSERT
        OS-->>OC: OrderDto
        OC-->>App: 200 OK
    end

    Note over App,DB: Route/station assignment: POST /api/StudentBusAssignment/Create (separate business flow).
